SENTENCE well ,  the answer is  the dynamics of earth's motions ,  the same thing that caused the ice age by the way .
SENTENCE the earth's not always the same distance from the sun ,  and it's not always tilting toward the sun at the same angle .
SENTENCE there are slight variations in these two parameters .
SENTENCE they're gradual variations but their effects can be pretty abrupt .
